-- UN Panel Told Ivory Coast Forces Killed 173, Tortured 90 From Dec. 16-21
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-12-23T10:50:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-23/un-panel-told-ivory-coast-forces-killed-173-tortured-90-from-dec-16-21.html
Ivory Coast’s security forces killed
173 people and subjected 90 to torture or ill treatment in the
last week, Agence France-Presse reported, citing the United
Nations deputy human rights chief,  Kyung-wha Kang .  UN human rights officers also substantiated allegations
that 471 people were detained and 24 disappeared between Dec. 16
and Dec. 21, Kang told a special session of the UN Human Rights
Council in Geneva today, the news service reported.  Laurent Gbagbo’s security forces on Dec. 16 fired on
opposition supporters who were protesting his refusal to accept
defeat in the Nov. 28 presidential election.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Franz Wild  in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Hirschberg at 
 phirschberg@bloomberg.net . 